  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (359dd77 2022-09-15T00:04:51.833948Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge test --match \"test_optimism_relay\" -vvv\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nNot sure what exactly is causing this, but it seems after switching forks a bunch in persistent contracts and then calling into any vm cheatcode it causes a non-descript crash, but only with verbose logs:\r\n\r\n```\r\nThe application panicked (crashed).\r\nMessage:  Disconnected trace\r\nLocation: evm/src/trace/mod.rs:72\r\n```\r\n\r\nPlease note that if you test without the `-vvv` modifier it successfully executes and completes.\r\n\r\nThe line that will cause the crash is here: https://github.com/makerdao/dss-test/blob/749d07e3b17e4a9762553ce92e19c557fca461c7/src/tests/IntegrationTest.t.sol#L146",
